<mod xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns="http://www.phpbb.com/mods/xml/modx-1.2.5.xsd">
	<header>
		<meta name="generator" content="MODX file generated with PP MODX Creator by tumba25 (online version)"/>
		<license><![CDATA[http://opensource.org/licenses/gpl-license.php GNU General Public License v2]]></license>
		<title lang="en"><![CDATA[Simple Payal]]></title>
		<description lang="en"><![CDATA[Adds an extra page to you forum software to allow paypal payment, with muiltiple currencies.]]></description>
		<author-notes lang="en"><![CDATA[You will need to have a paypal account for this mod to work.]]></author-notes>
		<author-group>
			<author>
				<realname><![CDATA[Richard Hayes]]></realname>
				<username><![CDATA[Richazey]]></username>
				<homepage><![CDATA[http://thehazey.co.uk]]></homepage>
				<email><![CDATA[richayes@talktalk.net]]></email>
			</author>
		</author-group>
		<mod-version>1.0.0</mod-version>
		<installation>
			<level>easy</level>
			<time>600</time>
			<target-version>3.0.7-PL1</target-version>
		</installation>
		<history>
			<entry>
				<date>2010-04-01</date>
				<rev-version>1.0.0</rev-version>
				<changelog lang="en">
					<change><![CDATA[First Release]]></change>
				</changelog>
			</entry>
		</history>
	</header>
	<action-group>
		<copy>
			<file from="root/paypal.php" to="paypal.php"/>
			<file from="root/language/en/mods/paypal.php" to="language/en/mods/paypal.php"/>
			<file from="root/styles/prosilver/template/paypal_body.html" to="styles/prosilver/template/paypal_body.html"/>
			<file from="root/styles/prosilver/theme/images/paypal.gif" to="styles/prosilver/theme/images/paypal.gif"/>
		</copy>
		<open src="viewonline.php">
			<edit>
				<find><![CDATA[		default:
			$location = $user->lang['INDEX'];
			$location_url = append_sid("{$phpbb_root_path}index.$phpEx");
		break;]]></find>
			</edit>
			<edit>
				<action type="before-add"><![CDATA[		case 'paypal':
			$user->add_lang('mods/paypal');
			$location = $user->lang['VIEWING_PAYPAL'];
			$location_url = append_sid("{$phpbb_root_path}paypal.$phpEx");
		break;]]></action>
			</edit>
		</open>
		<open src="includes/functions.php">
			<edit>
				<find><![CDATA[		'U_INDEX'				=> append_sid("{$phpbb_root_path}index.$phpEx"),]]></find>
			</edit>
			<edit>
				<action type="after-add"><![CDATA[		'U_PAYPAL'				=> append_sid("{$phpbb_root_path}paypal.$phpEx"),]]></action>
			</edit>
		</open>
		<open src="styles/prosilver/template/overall_footer.html">
			<edit>
				<find><![CDATA[<li class="rightside">]]></find>
			</edit>
			<edit>
				<inline-edit>
					<inline-action type="after-add"><![CDATA[<a href="{U_PAYPAL}">{L_PAYPAL}</a> &bull;]]></inline-action>
				</inline-edit>
			</edit>
		</open>
		<diy-instructions lang="en"><![CDATA[After adding the files and doing the above edits, you will need to open the styles/prosilver/template/paypal_body.html file and add your email address.
Find <input type="hidden" name="business" value="xxx@paypal.com" />
And where it says xxx@paypal.com you will need to replace it with your email address.

If you currency is not GBP you can change it so your currency is the one displayed on the drop down box by again opening the styles/prosilver/template/paypal_body.html file and
FIND <option value="GBP" selected="selected">{L_GBP}</option>
Where it says selected="selected" remove this and then add it to your currency.

You cna change the text by editing the language paypal.php file
Don't forget to refresh your template and purge the cache.]]></diy-instructions>
	</action-group>
</mod>
